390
00:28:06,501 --> 00:28:09,938
No. 'Cause you're not dull,
you're nice.

391
00:28:09,971 --> 00:28:12,207
That's what I thought.
I mean, I'm a happy lad.

392
00:28:13,641 --> 00:28:15,009
Or I was.

393
00:28:15,043 --> 00:28:17,579
Till me best friend started
acting the gilly-gooly.

394
00:28:18,079 --> 00:28:20,081
It's him, Padraic.

395
00:28:20,816 --> 00:28:23,284
Maybe he's just depressed.

396
00:28:23,318 --> 00:28:26,921
(WHISPERS) That's what I
was thinking, that he's depressed.

397
00:28:28,490 --> 00:28:29,391
(NORMALLY) Well, if he is,

398
00:28:29,424 --> 00:28:30,726
he could at least
keep it to himself, like.

399
00:28:30,760 --> 00:28:32,526
You know, push it down,
like the rest of us.

400
00:28:32,559 --> 00:28:34,027
(COWBELL JINGLES)

401
00:28:34,729 --> 00:28:36,731
No, Jenny!
(SNAPS FINGERS) Out!

402
00:28:36,765 --> 00:28:38,065
(COWBELL JINGLES)
Out!

403
00:28:40,134 --> 00:28:41,870
She just wants
a bit of company, Siobhan.

404
00:28:41,902 --> 00:28:43,537
Animals is for outside,
I've told ya.

405
00:28:43,570 --> 00:28:44,571
(CHUCKLES LIGHTLY)

406
00:28:48,409 --> 00:28:52,513
And people don't be laughing
at me behind me back,

407
00:28:52,546 --> 00:28:53,848
do they?

408
00:28:53,882 --> 00:28:55,149
No. Why would they be?

409
00:28:55,182 --> 00:28:57,584
They don't think
I'm dim or anything?

410
00:28:58,352 --> 00:28:59,353
Dim?

411
00:28:59,888 --> 00:29:01,088
No.

412
00:29:02,690 --> 00:29:04,158
You don't seem
very sure about it.

413
00:29:04,191 --> 00:29:06,059
Of course, I'm sure about it.

414
00:29:07,661 --> 00:29:10,130
Dominic's the dim one
on the island, isn't he?

415
00:29:10,865 --> 00:29:13,300
He is, aye. By miles.

416
00:29:14,869 --> 00:29:17,103
Uh, hang on, by miles.

417
00:29:17,136 --> 00:29:18,806
And then,
who's the next dimmest?

418
00:29:18,839 --> 00:29:20,173
Well, I don't like
to judge people

419
00:29:20,206 --> 00:29:21,441
in those terms now, do I?

420
00:29:21,474 --> 00:29:23,042
In what terms?
In order of their dimness.

421
00:29:23,075 --> 00:29:24,878
Well, I know you don't.
And neither do I, do I?

422
00:29:24,912 --> 00:29:25,945
But try, like.
No!

423
00:29:25,978 --> 00:29:27,380
I won't try.

424
00:29:27,413 --> 00:29:30,583
There's enough judgy people
on this fecking island, so no!

425
00:29:30,616 --> 00:29:31,551
You're not dim!

426
00:29:31,584 --> 00:29:34,420
You're a nice man, all right?
So, move on!

427
00:29:36,690 --> 00:29:37,925
I'm as clever as you, anyways.

428
00:29:37,957 --> 00:29:39,058
I know that at least.

429
00:29:39,091 --> 00:29:41,260
(UNDER BREATH) Yeah,
don't be fecking stupid.

430
00:29:41,561 --> 00:29:42,863
Huh?

431
