with ye the night?

445
00:30:48,860 --> 00:30:50,261
Just for the one night, like?

446
00:30:50,729 --> 00:30:52,229
SIOBHAN: Mm...

447
00:30:52,263 --> 00:30:55,000
Well, just the one night, mind.

448
00:30:55,032 --> 00:30:57,769
Nice! I'll see ye
for supper, so.

449
00:30:57,802 --> 00:30:59,336
(CHUCKLES) Whoo-hoo!

450
00:31:07,511 --> 00:31:11,081
(PRAYING IN LATIN)

451
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:18,522
(GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING)

452
00:31:33,837 --> 00:31:35,706
(WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY)

453
00:31:43,246 --> 00:31:44,581
Forgive me, Father,
for I have sinned.

454
00:31:44,614 --> 00:31:47,383
It's eight weeks since
my last confession, I think.

455
00:31:48,052 --> 00:31:49,652
Go on, Colm.

456
00:31:49,687 --> 00:31:52,056
(SIGHS) Just the usual,
I suppose, Father.

457
00:31:52,088 --> 00:31:55,191
The drinking
and the impure thoughts.

458
00:31:55,224 --> 00:31:56,694
And a bit of pride, I suppose.

459
00:31:56,727 --> 00:32:00,363
Although I never really saw that
as a sin, but sure I'm here now.

460
00:32:01,297 --> 00:32:02,298
And

461
00:32:03,232 --> 00:32:05,201
how's the despair?

462
00:32:06,102 --> 00:32:08,839
Not so much of it of late.
Thanks be.

463
00:32:10,941 --> 00:32:13,643
And why aren't you talking to
Padraic Suilleabhain no more?

464
00:32:16,144 --> 00:32:17,947
That wouldn't be a sin, now,
would it, Father?

465
00:32:17,981 --> 00:32:22,317
It wouldn't be a sin, no, but
it's not very nice either, is it?

466
00:32:23,619 --> 00:32:25,621
Who told you?

467
00:32:25,654 --> 00:32:28,725
It's an island, Colm.
Word gets around.

468
00:32:30,158 --> 00:32:33,362
